Global Veterinary Splints Market Insights
Veterinary Splints Market size was valued at USD 1.5 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 2.8 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 8.5% from 2024 to 2030.

Veterinary Splints Market Overview
The global veterinary splints market has been experiencing significant growth due to increasing awareness about animal healthcare, rising veterinary expenditures, and advancements in splinting technologies. As of 2024, the market size is estimated to reach approximately USD 1.2 billion, and it is expected to grow at a CAGR of 7.2% from 2025 to 2030. The adoption of veterinary splints for the treatment of fractures and injuries in pets and livestock is expected to remain a key growth driver. The rising demand for orthopedic and post-surgical rehabilitation solutions is further propelling the market forward.

